Judy Foster - Helper.......This will be our last reading for 2012
Assisted by Judy Foster - Partly cloudy- but bright.
Assisted by Judy Foster Beautiful- cool sunny day
Beautiful- sunny fall day. Slight southerly breeze. Assister by Judy Foster
Assited by Judy Foster. Another beautiful fall day! The water is calm. We saw a bald eagle soaring over the lake. This is the final reading for this season. See you in the spring!

Assisted by Judy Foster. Water is taking on same brackish hue as lakes C + D. E Lake is normally very clear. Water appears to have a lot of suspended particulate in it. Last week the presence of Zebra Mussels was confirmed in Lake Morris by the DNR.
Assisted by Judy Foster. Lake E is also somewhat brackish.
Assisted by Judy Foster. This is the only lake in the chain that still has a slightly brackish appearance.

Assisted by Judy Foster. Zebra Mussel monitoring plates installed July 26- 2014 on my pier by Golden Sands R+D. This is normally a very clear lake. But this year it has been murky with what appears to be a lot of fine particulate suspended in the water.
Lake "E" Emerald has finally cleared up. It was brackish and murky most of the summer.
Assisted by Judy Foster Assisted by Judy Foster
